#
# pob-TZVP-rev2  (revised all-electron basis for solid-state calculations)
#
# Triple-zeta valence + polarization, BSSE-corrected.  The elements in this
# file are taken from four papers; the ranges below give the source of each:
#
# H-Br  (periods 1-4):
# D. Vilela Oliveira, M. F. Peintinger, J. Laun, T. Bredow,
# "BSSE-correction scheme for consistent Gaussian basis sets of double- and
#  triple-zeta valence with polarization quality for solid-state calculations",
# J. Comput. Chem. 2019, 40, 2364-2376.  DOI: 10.1002/jcc.26013
#
# Rb-I  (period 5):
#   J. Laun, T. Bredow,
#   "BSSE-corrected consistent Gaussian basis sets of triple-zeta valence with
#    polarization quality of the fifth period for solid-state calculations",
#   J. Comput. Chem. 2022, 43, 839-846.  DOI: 10.1002/jcc.26839
#
# Cs, Ba, Hf-Po  (period 6):
#   J. Laun, T. Bredow,
#   "BSSE-corrected consistent Gaussian basis sets of triple-zeta valence with
#    polarization quality of the sixth period for solid-state calculations",
#   J. Comput. Chem. 2021.  DOI: 10.1002/jcc.26521
#
# La-Lu  (lanthanides):
#   L. M. Seidler, J. Laun, T. Bredow,
#   "BSSE-corrected consistent Gaussian basis sets of triple-zeta valence
#    quality of the lanthanides La-Lu for solid-state calculations",
#   J. Comput. Chem. 2023.  DOI: 10.1002/jcc.27097
#
# Converted verbatim from the TURBOMOLE basen library (per-element blocks)
# into pyscf NWChem .dat format; exponents and contraction coefficients are
# unchanged.
#

